coder v0.0.0-devel

USAGE:
  coder exp sync timeline [flags]

  Show a timeline of unit state changes

  Show every recorded unit state transition and dependency declaration across
  all units, in the order they occurred. The default output is an ASCII graph of
  the dependency DAG in event-time order; use --output json for the raw event
  list. With --watch, new rows are streamed as events occur until interrupted.

OPTIONS:
  -o, --output text|json (default: text)
          Output format.

  -w, --watch bool
          Stream new rows as events occur until interrupted.

———
Run `coder --help` for a list of global options.
